# VISUALify Project

Real-time Spotify music visualization web app.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- D3.js (visualization)
- Tailwind CSS (styling)
- Zustand (state)
- NextAuth.js (auth)
- Vercel (hosting)

## Key Constraints
- NO Pages Router - use App Router only
- NO `any` types - use proper TypeScript
- NO Redux - use Zustand
- NO separate CSS files for components - use Tailwind
- NO class components - use functional components only

## File Locations
- Pages: `src/app/`
- Components: `src/components/`
- Hooks: `src/hooks/`
- Utils: `src/lib/`
- Stores: `src/stores/`
- Types: `src/types/`

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`PulseMode.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useNowPlaying.ts`)
- Stores: camelCase with `use` prefix (`usePlayerStore.ts`)
- Utils: camelCase (`beatClock.ts`, `colors.ts`)

## Import Aliases
Use `@/` prefix for all imports:
```tsx
import { PulseMode } from '@/components/visualizer';
import { usePlayerStore } from '@/stores';
```

## D3 Usage Pattern
D3 handles math/data mapping; Canvas 2D handles rendering. D3 never touches the DOM directly in visualizer modes.
- `d3-ease` — Beat decay curves (easeExpOut) in BeatClock
- `d3-scale` — Mapping audio features (0-1) to visual params (sizes, colors, speeds)
- `d3-interpolate` — Smooth HSL color blending based on valence

## Documentation
Read project docs in `/docs` folder before implementing features.
